00:00:48.535 --> 00:00:54.165
that sum to negative 4. Those factors are negative 6, and positive 2. We set

00:00:54.165 --> 00:00:57.850
each factor equal to 0 to get x equals 6, or x equals negative 2 as our

00:00:57.850 --> 00:01:04.671
potential solutions to the original radical equation. Finally, we check each of

00:01:04.671 --> 00:01:09.699
the solutions in the original equation and discover they both check. This means

